messages.text: Jenn stands before Cal, her lips still tingling from their kiss.
What do you mean, you can‚Äôt do this?
Cal runs a hand through his thick hair.
I just‚Ä¶I just can‚Äôt.
But I thought you said you forgave me‚Ä¶
Is this because you‚Äôre dating Selena?
This doesn‚Äôt have anything to do with her.
Is it the other women on Spark, then?
Since when are you the jealous type?
Since you‚Äôve got bikini-clad women falling all over you.
I‚Äôm sure you‚Äôve got guys hitting on you all the time, too.
Are you kidding me?
The only man who even acknowledges my existence is the UPS guy‚Äî
And that‚Äôs only because I order too much from Amazon.
I‚Äôm sure that‚Äôs not true. We both know you‚Äôre out of my league.
Please. You‚Äôre a catch! You‚Äôre a smokin‚Äô hot doctor who takes care of sick kids, and you‚Äôre ridiculously nice.
You pick up the bill AND you drive a Porsche‚Äî
Of course every woman you meet is going to want to screw your brains out.
When you put it that way, my life sounds pretty good. Why change it?
Cal!
I‚Äôm kidding. But seriously ‚Äî you think I‚Äôm hot?
You can bounce a baby off those abs.
As a pediatric surgeon, I wouldn‚Äôt recommend that.
Unable to help herself, Jenn laughs.
And you‚Äôre funny, too. How is this even fair?
Cal shrugs.
We‚Äôre so good together. Why can‚Äôt we just start over?
Cal takes Jenn‚Äôs hand.
Part of me wants to, but I just‚Ä¶don‚Äôt know.
When you broke up with me, it nearly killed me.
Tears spring to Jenn‚Äôs eyes.
I was so certain you were the one. When you left me‚Ä¶
Cal bites his lip.
I‚Äôm so sorry.
Not your fault. But‚Ä¶it‚Äôs just‚Ä¶if we got back together, and you got bored with me‚Ä¶
I won‚Äôt go through that again. I can‚Äôt.
But I won‚Äôt get bored of you!
Can you actually promise me that?
Jenn drops his hand and takes a step back.
You left me because you were bored and unhappy‚Äî
Now you want me back because you‚Äôre bored and unhappy.
That‚Äôs not it.
Isn‚Äôt it, though?
I look new and exciting because I lost weight, and I travel, and girls are interested in me now, and I got this nice shiny car‚Ä¶
Jenn, maybe you just like bright and shiny things.
But I can‚Äôt be bright and shiny all the time.
You‚Äôre making me sound awful.
I promise you‚Äôre not awful. You‚Äôre beautiful, and hilarious and perfect‚Äî
You‚Äôre smart and funny and fantastic company. You play a seriously mean piano. You write your own songs!
All those reasons and more were why I wanted to marry you‚Äî
But you didn‚Äôt even want to talk about getting engaged.
Maybe I‚Äôm ready now.
Cal stares at Jenn a long time.
Are you?
I don‚Äôt know.
Cal sighs and backs away.
I can‚Äôt do this.
Please, Cal. Give me a chance. Don‚Äôt you still care about me?
Of course I do.
Then, what‚Äôs the problem?
When we were together, I never tried to change you.
I didn‚Äôt care if you gained or lost thirty pounds.
Or if you cut your hair or not, what car you drove, where you lived, or what music you listened to‚Äî
I loved YOU for you. And I would‚Äôve kept on loving you for you.
I didn‚Äôt try to change you!
Really? What about the iPod?
Cal, everybody listens to music on their phone!
Yeah, but I liked my mini iPod. It fit perfectly in my pocket. But it drove you nuts! So I got rid of it, remember?
I didn‚Äôt realize it meant that much to you.
All I ever wanted was for you to be happy.
I‚Äôm a terrible person.
No, you‚Äôre not. I just think you‚Äôre not happy with yourself right now‚Äî
And that makes you unhappy with other people.
I don‚Äôt understand what you‚Äôre saying right now.
You think that if you fix other people, it‚Äôll fix your life‚Äî
But you don‚Äôt realize that you have to fix yourself first.
You hate your job. You should quit it and do what you love.
I can‚Äôt just write songs, Cal. I won‚Äôt make any money.
But won‚Äôt you be happy?
You have to be happy with yourself before you can be happy with anyone else.
That‚Äôs the one good thing our breakup taught me.
What am I supposed to do? Quit my job?
Go up to Beyonce and tell her I‚Äôve got a sick new beat for her?
Why not?
A thousand reasons. First of which ‚Äî I don‚Äôt know Beyonce.
How can you commit to me, when you won‚Äôt commit to yourself?
Cal, please.
I can‚Äôt, Jenn. I‚Äôm sorry.
Cal opens his car door and ducks inside.
He glances at her through the window.
Seconds later, he‚Äôs pulling out of the parking lot.
Jenn, numb, slips into her own car.
Her phone pings.
How‚Äôs the date going?
Rotten. It‚Äôs over already.
He hates me.
No, he doesn‚Äôt. And if he does, I‚Äôm going to beat him up. Let me call him‚Ä¶
DAD! No!
He told me that I only want him back because I‚Äôm bored and unhappy.
He might have a point there.
Whose side are you on?!
Yours. Always, pumpkin. So, he‚Äôs acting gunshy?
He thinks I‚Äôm going to break his heart again.
Are you?
Not on purpose.
#WeakTea.
What should I do?
Figure out what you really want so you don‚Äôt string him along. Do you love him?
I think so. I hate the thought of Cal with anyone else.
He‚Äôs probably heading over to Selena‚Äôs place right now.
No, he‚Äôs not. He‚Äôs texting me.
What‚Äôs he SAYING?
That‚Äôs private. Also, he officially broke it off with Selena yesterday. He told me so.
He did?!
Yeah, he said he had feelings for you and it wasn‚Äôt fair to Selena.
What‚Äôs he saying right now?
Why don‚Äôt you ask him yourself?
